txt.en: 'Ah! There remains no place to run, Orc!'
Instance: The Road to Dunharrow
'Orc, your disguise makes no fool of me!'
'Nay! Run no further, [placeholder].'
'The Orc will find no shelter there.'
'As it was with Baldor of old, those paths lead to naught but death.'
'Queer, indeed, that they would think the Dead an ally of any...'
'You should never have disturbed the Dead!'
'You did that yourself, Woman!'
'These stones... never have I been within the Dimholt.'
'Ah, at last, Dunharrow! We have made it!'
'We shall slay your people to the last...'
'I know not what we will find, so ready your wits.'
'Your efforts in the Harrowdale afforded us a swift and safe journey.'
'...just as you would have done to us!'
'You have my thanks, [placeholder].'
'For my part, I have set the people on building up our shelter...'
'S-stay back! Stay away from me!'
'...for there remain many from the Westfold who have yet to rally here.'
'Long have I known the tale of the Men who live under the Dwimorberg...'
'Their work shall take some time, so let us walk.'
'...but never have they ventured from their dark paths.'
'I wished not to alarm the people, but I must speak plainly...'
'Still... I fear something watches us nearby.'
'I believe we are being watched, [placeholder].'
'The canopy smothers the light, and we must not be caught unawares.'
'We must discover what lurks beyond the trees.'
'We have been ambushed, [placeholder]!'
'I hear more! Slay them all!'
'Are these the Orcs you spoke of?'
'Swiftly now! We cannot let it escape!'
'Naught but the creaking of branches, [placeholder].'
'Wait -- what is that?'
'Perhaps I was mistaken...'
'We must press on!'
'Wait -- what is that?'
